
================== GETX MISTAKES & CORRECTIONS ==================

This is a clean, all-in-one cheat sheet for common GetX mistakes
and how to fix them. Copy everything as one block.

--------------------------------------------------------------
1Ô∏è‚É£ Using @override on variables ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
@override
final ProductController controller = Get.put(ProductController());

Correct:
final ProductController controller = Get.put(ProductController());
// @override is only for methods, not variables.

--------------------------------------------------------------
2Ô∏è‚É£ Creating controllers inside pages ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
final cartController = Get.put(CartController());
// Creates a new controller every time the page opens.

Correct:
Get.put(CartController()); // create once at root
final cartController = Get.find<CartController>(); // reuse in pages

--------------------------------------------------------------
3Ô∏è‚É£ Using Get.find() before Get.put() ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
final cartController = Get.find<CartController>();
// controller not created yet ‚Üí crash

Correct:
Get.put(CartController()); // create first
final cartController = Get.find<CartController>(); // find safely

--------------------------------------------------------------
4Ô∏è‚É£ Using Get.arguments outside build() ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
ProductMod product = Get.arguments;

Correct:
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  final ProductMod product = Get.arguments;
}
// Arguments are available only during widget build.

--------------------------------------------------------------
5Ô∏è‚É£ Passing objects directly to Text() ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
Text(item)

Correct:
Text(item.name)
// Text() requires a String, not an object

--------------------------------------------------------------
6Ô∏è‚É£ Not typing RxList ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
RxList product = <ProductMod>[].obs;

Correct:
RxList<ProductMod> product = <ProductMod>[].obs;
// Provides type safety and prevents runtime errors

--------------------------------------------------------------
7Ô∏è‚É£ Adding fake data to cart ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
prod.add(ProductMod(name: 'name', price: 34));

Correct:
void addToCart(ProductMod product) {
  cart.add(product);
}

cartController.addToCart(product);
// Always pass the selected product

--------------------------------------------------------------
8Ô∏è‚É£ Missing Obx for reactive UI ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
ListView.builder(...)
// UI will not update when data changes

Correct:
Obx(() => ListView.builder(...))
// Observables must be wrapped in Obx

--------------------------------------------------------------
9Ô∏è‚É£ Mixing responsibilities in controllers ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong:
ProductController manages cart items

Correct:
ProductController ‚Üí Products
CartController ‚Üí Cart
// Separation of concerns improves maintainability

--------------------------------------------------------------
üîü Misunderstanding GetX lifecycle ‚ùå
--------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong assumption:
Get.put() can be used anywhere

Correct:
Get.put() ‚Üí create once at root
Get.find() ‚Üí access anywhere else

--------------------------------------------------------------
üß† FINAL GETX RULES (MEMORIZE)
--------------------------------------------------------------
1. Controllers live once
2. Pages do not own state
3. Get.put() only once
4. Get.find() everywhere else
5. Always use Obx with Rx
6. Pass real data, not dummy data

--------------------------------------------------------------
üéØ RESULT
--------------------------------------------------------------
‚úî Clean architecture
‚úî Correct GetX lifecycle
‚úî Reactive UI
‚úî No duplicate controllers
‚úî Production-ready structure



